The paper deals with a matrix factorization problem, which is a common topic in machine learning and data analysis. The use of non-negative matrices and the separability assumption suggest that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The mention of text analysis and image processing also suggests that the paper may belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of dequantizing techniques and the mention of polynomial time and exponential speedup suggest that the paper may belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation).
